Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pop the @diced sweet potato{200%g} onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out
in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden,
~{16-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with
@salt{0.25%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a
#lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Cut the @lime{1/2} into wedges. Cut the @medium tomatoes{2} into 1cm chunks.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine a good squeeze of lime juice, @sugar{1%tsp} and
@olive oil{1%tbsp} for the salsa.

Stir the tomato chunks into the salsa dressing. Season with @salt{} and
@black pepper{}.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a sieve.

Pop the (now empty) #frying pan{} back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of
@oil{}. Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and fry until it starts to
brown, ~{3-4%minutes}, then add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the black beans, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @chipotle paste{20%g},
@tomato passata{1%carton}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce.
Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Lightly crush half of the beans in the pan using a #potato masher{}, then
lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @butter{20%g} until melted.

Once the sweet potato has roasted, stir it through the beans with a squeeze
of lime juice.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed.

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the chipotle chorizo, sweet potato and black beans. Sprinkle over
the cheese.

Top with the tomato salsa. Finish with any remaining lime wedges. Enjoy!